00:00:21.548 --> 00:00:26.987 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>Hi! I'm Usagi Tsukino! It</i>
 <i>may not look it, but I'm a</i>
 <i>Guardian of justice! </i>

00:00:27.021 --> 00:00:32.694 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>I use a special brooch to</i>
 <i>transform and fight evil! </i>

00:00:36.031 --> 00:00:40.503 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>You know me as the Pretty</i>
 <i>Guardian who fights for love</i>
 <i>and for justice.</i>

00:00:40.536 --> 00:00:43.340 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>I am Sailor Moon!</i>

00:00:45.744 --> 00:00:48.879 position:13% line:83% align:start
And... these guys here are
my friends...!

00:00:48.912 --> 00:00:53.719 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Ami Mizuno, the kindhearted</i>
 <i>genius! </i>

00:00:53.753 --> 00:00:56.555 position:19% line:89% align:start
I am Sailor Mercury!

00:00:58.424 --> 00:01:02.729 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>Rei Hino, the hotheaded</i>
 <i>psychic! </i>

00:01:02.763 --> 00:01:04.766 position:24% line:89% align:start
I am Sailor Mars!

00:01:07.602 --> 00:01:11.272 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Makoto Kino, the master of</i>
 <i>cooking and cleaning! </i>

00:01:12.073 --> 00:01:14.643 position:19% line:89% align:start
I am Sailor Jupiter!

00:01:16.078 --> 00:01:20.049 position:27% line:77% align:start
 <i>And Minako Aino,</i>
 <i>once known as the crime</i>
 <i>fighter Sailor V! </i>

00:01:21.451 --> 00:01:23.487 position:21% line:89% align:start
I am Sailor Venus!

00:01:25.756 --> 00:01:27.625 position:19% line:89% align:start
Together, we five...

00:01:27.658 --> 00:01:30.294 position:13% line:83% align:start
...are known as the Sailor
Guardians!

00:01:31.696 --> 00:01:35.434 position:10% line:77% align:start
And you can leave it to all
of us to protect the peace
on Earth!

00:01:35.668 --> 00:01:37.437 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:03:16.552 --> 00:03:26.764 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:03:28.265 --> 00:03:31.469 position:5% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:03:41.180 --> 00:03:42.950 position:33% line:89% align:start
[chuckling]

00:03:42.983 --> 00:03:44.150 position:30% line:89% align:start
Thank you...

00:03:45.686 --> 00:03:48.590 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>One day, I'll come back</i>
 <i>with lots of flowers for</i>
 <i>you, too! </i>

00:03:54.964 --> 00:03:58.935 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sobbing]

00:03:58.969 --> 00:04:04.541 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>Please don't cry. I promise</i>
 <i>that when I come back, I'll</i>
 <i>bring you lots of flowers...</i>

00:04:04.574 --> 00:04:05.910 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>So please... </i>

00:04:06.978 --> 00:04:09.847 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>... Don't forget me.</i>

00:04:09.880 --> 00:04:11.148 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh!

00:04:11.182 --> 00:04:11.917 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh...?

00:04:11.950 --> 00:04:14.686 position:5% line:83% align:start
The meaning behind
forget-me-nots.

00:04:14.720 --> 00:04:16.555 position:44% line:89% align:start
Oh!

00:04:17.155 --> 00:04:18.625 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>"Don't forget me..." </i>

00:04:19.993 --> 00:04:21.628 position:5% line:89% align:start
That's not all.

00:04:21.661 --> 00:04:22.863 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:04:22.896 --> 00:04:26.634 position:5% line:77% align:start
It's also said that
forget-me-nots symbolize...
true love.

00:04:27.134 --> 00:04:29.638 position:19% line:89% align:start
You sure know a lot!

00:04:29.671 --> 00:04:32.273 position:5% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:04:41.885 --> 00:04:42.986 position:24% line:89% align:start
[clearing throat]

00:04:47.659 --> 00:04:50.261 position:10% line:83% align:start
That Usagi, flirting with my
Mamo!

00:04:51.029 --> 00:04:54.232 position:19% line:83% align:start
And right out in broad
daylight, too!

00:04:54.667 --> 00:04:56.902 position:5% line:83% align:start
We shouldn't spy on them!
You guys...!

00:04:56.935 --> 00:04:59.638 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's just wrong! It's wrong!

00:04:59.873 --> 00:05:00.140 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:05:00.172 --> 00:05:01.240 position:5% line:89% align:start
What?!

00:05:01.273 --> 00:05:02.308 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hey!

00:05:02.342 --> 00:05:04.845 position:13% line:83% align:start
Shh! They're just about to
get to the good part!

00:05:04.879 --> 00:05:06.647 position:33% line:89% align:start
[struggling]

00:05:07.213 --> 00:05:11.787 position:5% line:77% align:start
I'm telling you guys, this
isn't right! Spying is just
wrong!

00:05:11.820 --> 00:05:14.890 position:13% line:77% align:start
Oh, yeah? Then why are you
still hanging around here,
Ami?

00:05:14.923 --> 00:05:15.824 position:33% line:89% align:start
[squirming]

00:05:15.857 --> 00:05:19.327 position:13% line:83% align:start
C-Chibi-Usa, don't wiggle
around so much!

00:05:19.361 --> 00:05:22.265 position:27% line:89% align:start
Uh---[chuckling]

00:05:32.077 --> 00:05:38.050 position:35% line:89% align:start
[groaning]

00:05:38.718 --> 00:05:39.852 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm?

00:05:43.757 --> 00:05:49.329 position:16% line:89% align:start
[screaming and panting]

00:05:49.362 --> 00:05:55.738 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughing]

00:05:55.771 --> 00:05:58.007 position:19% line:89% align:start
That wasn't funny...!

00:05:58.041 --> 00:06:01.077 position:10% line:89% align:start
Mamo...? Where did he go?!

00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:04.748 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sighing]

00:06:21.701 --> 00:06:24.838 position:33% line:89% align:start
Huh? Wha...

00:06:30.211 --> 00:06:31.112 position:30% line:89% align:start
What's this?

00:06:31.146 --> 00:06:36.152 position:35% line:89% align:start
[giggling]

00:06:40.022 --> 00:06:42.726 position:35% line:89% align:start
[giggling]

00:06:44.027 --> 00:06:49.366 position:35% line:89% align:start
[giggling]

00:07:07.121 --> 00:07:10.158 position:16% line:83% align:start
Mamo! Mamo! Did you see
that?! The flowers?

00:07:10.192 --> 00:07:11.259 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Hey... </i>

00:07:11.293 --> 00:07:13.728 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's been a while, Mamoru.

00:07:17.300 --> 00:07:19.202 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's me.

00:07:19.235 --> 00:07:20.169 position:5% line:89% align:start
Do you know him?

00:07:20.203 --> 00:07:22.038 position:33% line:89% align:start
Huh? No...

00:07:22.072 --> 00:07:24.440 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry I made you wait.

00:07:24.473 --> 00:07:27.312 position:5% line:77% align:start
I feel really bad that it
took as much time as it
did...

00:07:27.344 --> 00:07:32.349 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>But...  I finally</i>
 <i>found a flower that will</i>
 <i>make you happy. </i>

00:07:32.383 --> 00:07:33.618 position:30% line:89% align:start
You what...?

00:07:33.651 --> 00:07:37.957 position:5% line:77% align:start
Come on! You didn't forget
the promise that we made,
did you?

00:07:37.990 --> 00:07:39.124 position:27% line:89% align:start
The promise...?

00:07:39.158 --> 00:07:42.729 position:5% line:77% align:start
That's right. The flower
that we promised to each
other.

00:07:51.505 --> 00:07:53.876 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sorry! You can't have him!

00:07:53.909 --> 00:07:58.447 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's just that Mamo is my
boyfriend.

00:07:58.480 --> 00:07:59.349 position:35% line:89% align:start
Move it.

00:08:00.216 --> 00:08:01.483 position:30% line:89% align:start
Huh? [gasping]

00:08:02.819 --> 00:08:03.953 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:08:04.487 --> 00:08:07.057 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:08:07.091 --> 00:08:07.523 position:38% line:89% align:start
Usako!

00:08:07.558 --> 00:08:08.792 position:38% line:89% align:start
Usagi!

00:08:12.496 --> 00:08:14.532 position:10% line:83% align:start
Hey, you! Where do you think
you're going?!

00:08:14.566 --> 00:08:17.469 position:19% line:77% align:start
You get back here and
apologize to her, you
jerk!

00:08:17.502 --> 00:08:21.275 position:5% line:83% align:start
Mamoru, I will fulfill our
promise to each other.

00:08:25.078 --> 00:08:28.515 position:33% line:89% align:start
[struggling]

00:08:28.548 --> 00:08:30.184 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:08:43.465 --> 00:08:44.501 position:30% line:89% align:start
He's gone...

00:08:45.168 --> 00:08:47.804 position:16% line:89% align:start
Fiore...? It can't be!

00:08:48.471 --> 00:08:50.074 position:5% line:89% align:start
Mamo, what...?

00:08:52.009 --> 00:08:56.548 position:19% line:77% align:start
 <i>And now onto our next</i>
 <i>story... Today at 2 p.m., it</i>
 <i>was discovered that a giant</i>

00:08:56.581 --> 00:08:59.584 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>asteroid is about to pass by</i>
 <i>close to Earth. </i>

00:08:59.618 --> 00:09:03.256 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>Researchers calculate that</i>
 <i>the massive rock will be</i>
 <i>making its closest approach</i>

00:09:03.289 --> 00:09:05.658 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>tomorrow night at 11:20 p.m.</i>

00:09:05.692 --> 00:09:09.163 position:13% line:77% align:start
However, it will still be
twenty-five hundred and
fifty million kilometers

00:09:09.196 --> 00:09:12.267 position:16% line:83% align:start
away, so it will have no
direct effect on the Earth.

00:09:12.300 --> 00:09:15.438 position:10% line:77% align:start
If you have an astronomical
telescope, you can observe
the-

00:09:16.272 --> 00:09:19.642 position:13% line:77% align:start
Seems the observatories on
Earth have finally noticed
it, too.

00:09:19.675 --> 00:09:23.080 position:13% line:77% align:start
The asteroid you mentioned
before? It's not going to
hit Earth,

00:09:23.113 --> 00:09:24.081 position:19% line:89% align:start
so what's your worry?

00:09:24.114 --> 00:09:26.183 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's what we thought at
first as well...

00:09:26.216 --> 00:09:27.884 position:5% line:83% align:start
Is there some other
problem?

00:09:27.918 --> 00:09:31.022 position:10% line:83% align:start
Everyone, come here and take
a look at this.

00:09:35.327 --> 00:09:39.331 position:19% line:77% align:start
I used the computer to
perform my own analysis of
that asteroid.

00:09:39.366 --> 00:09:42.102 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>It spans over six hundred</i>
 <i>meters. </i>

00:09:42.135 --> 00:09:47.007 position:16% line:77% align:start
That's really big. If it
were to collide with Earth,
it would be a disaster.

00:09:47.040 --> 00:09:49.343 position:13% line:89% align:start
No, that's not the issue.

00:09:49.377 --> 00:09:53.482 position:16% line:77% align:start
Considering its size, it
has surprisingly little
mass. Meaning, if it

00:09:53.514 --> 00:09:56.218 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>fell to Earth, it'd just</i>
 <i>burn up in the atmosphere. </i>

00:09:56.251 --> 00:09:58.086 position:16% line:83% align:start
Then what exactly's the
problem?

00:09:58.120 --> 00:10:01.590 position:10% line:77% align:start
We picked up signs of plant
energy coming from the
asteroid.

00:10:01.623 --> 00:10:03.526 position:41% line:89% align:start
What?

00:10:03.559 --> 00:10:07.431 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>You know... now that you</i>
 <i>mention it... that asteroid</i>
 <i>does kind of look more like</i>

00:10:07.464 --> 00:10:09.700 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>a seed than a rock</i>
 <i>formation. </i>

00:10:09.733 --> 00:10:12.470 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm sure there's a simple
explanation for all this.

00:10:12.504 --> 00:10:15.006 position:5% line:83% align:start
Maybe there's just moss growing
on its surface.

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:19.011 position:16% line:77% align:start
Artemis, I think you're
making a big fuss over
nothing.

00:10:19.045 --> 00:10:20.446 position:5% line:89% align:start
Let's hope so...

00:10:20.479 --> 00:10:22.081 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Am I overreacting? </i>

00:10:22.114 --> 00:10:23.417 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:10:23.450 --> 00:10:25.685 position:35% line:89% align:start
[groaning]

00:10:25.719 --> 00:10:30.224 position:10% line:77% align:start
But he really did look like
more than just a...
"friend."

00:10:30.258 --> 00:10:31.092 position:44% line:89% align:start
No!

00:10:31.125 --> 00:10:33.294 position:16% line:83% align:start
There's no way that Mamo
would ever...!

00:10:33.327 --> 00:10:37.598 position:21% line:77% align:start
Mamoru did look very
serious when that guy
showed up.

00:10:37.632 --> 00:10:41.204 position:13% line:83% align:start
And then he suddenly said
that he needed to leave.

00:10:41.237 --> 00:10:46.109 position:13% line:77% align:start
Maybe Mamoru actually does
know that guy we saw at the
botanical garden, after all.

00:10:46.142 --> 00:10:48.578 position:5% line:83% align:start
Usagi, he didn't tell you
anything?

00:10:48.611 --> 00:10:51.315 position:33% line:89% align:start
Huh? No...

00:10:51.348 --> 00:10:55.020 position:27% line:77% align:start
Come to think of
it, I really don't
know much about Mamo...

00:10:55.053 --> 00:10:56.721 position:5% line:83% align:start
... from the time before
I met him.

00:10:56.755 --> 00:11:00.193 position:13% line:83% align:start
I guess Mamoru is popular
with the guys, as well.

00:11:00.226 --> 00:11:02.728 position:5% line:83% align:start
Ami, what are you
implying?!

00:11:02.762 --> 00:11:07.334 position:27% line:83% align:start
That's actually
an interesting thought, Ami.

00:11:07.367 --> 00:11:09.336 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, this meeting's as good
as over...

00:11:09.369 --> 00:11:10.405 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll say...

00:11:10.438 --> 00:11:11.738 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sighing]

00:11:11.772 --> 00:11:14.275 position:19% line:77% align:start
No! Of Course not?! I
mean, it's fine, if that's
who you are.

00:11:14.309 --> 00:11:16.445 position:33% line:83% align:start
Oh, yeah. I
totally agree.

00:11:16.479 --> 00:11:20.116 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>I know some people at my</i>
 <i>school who are in that kind</i>
 <i>of relationship. </i>

00:11:20.149 --> 00:11:21.016 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Really?! </i>

00:11:27.558 --> 00:11:30.760 position:5% line:83% align:start
So... are these your
parents, Mamo?

00:11:30.794 --> 00:11:31.695 position:41% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:11:32.663 --> 00:11:35.766 position:5% line:83% align:start
You grew up alone, without
any family at all?

00:11:35.800 --> 00:11:36.801 position:30% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:11:36.834 --> 00:11:38.570 position:5% line:89% align:start
Were you lonely?

00:11:38.605 --> 00:11:41.707 position:30% line:77% align:start
Doesn't matter
anymore. You're my family
now.

00:11:42.408 --> 00:11:45.579 position:16% line:83% align:start
Looking back, I think I
needed to be alone...

00:11:45.613 --> 00:11:47.780 position:30% line:83% align:start
... so I could
meet you.

00:11:47.814 --> 00:11:49.049 position:5% line:89% align:start
Really?

00:11:53.355 --> 00:11:56.591 position:5% line:83% align:start
You're right... I am your
family.

00:11:56.825 --> 00:12:01.164 position:5% line:77% align:start
And from now on... I'll
always be here to protect
you.

00:12:02.598 --> 00:12:06.069 position:5% line:83% align:start
I guess you're an expert when it
comes to love, Ami!

00:12:06.103 --> 00:12:08.172 position:5% line:89% align:start
Me? No, I--

00:12:08.205 --> 00:12:11.074 position:21% line:83% align:start
Ami, you're so cute.
Speaking of love,

00:12:11.108 --> 00:12:13.677 position:16% line:77% align:start
did I ever tell you guys
about the guy who broke
my heart?

00:12:13.710 --> 00:12:15.046 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Mamo... </i>

00:12:53.924 --> 00:12:56.394 position:35% line:89% align:start
[yawning]

00:12:56.428 --> 00:13:00.600 position:13% line:77% align:start
Balancing being a student
and a Guardian of justice is
exhausting!

00:13:00.633 --> 00:13:04.770 position:5% line:77% align:start
Oh, give me a break! Our
meeting went nowhere because
you girls kept chitchatting

00:13:04.804 --> 00:13:05.706 position:5% line:89% align:start
all night long!

00:13:05.771 --> 00:13:06.306 position:38% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm!

00:13:06.340 --> 00:13:07.773 position:19% line:89% align:start
[chuckling nervously]

00:13:07.808 --> 00:13:10.777 position:13% line:83% align:start
Mako, thanks for making me
my lunch!

00:13:10.811 --> 00:13:12.680 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sure! You're very welcome.

00:13:12.714 --> 00:13:15.183 position:5% line:89% align:start
Ready for school, Chibi-Usa?

00:13:15.216 --> 00:13:16.585 position:38% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm!

00:13:17.553 --> 00:13:18.587 position:35% line:89% align:start
Huh...?

00:13:18.786 --> 00:13:19.822 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>What's wrong, Rei? </i>

00:13:19.855 --> 00:13:21.223 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:13:23.792 --> 00:13:27.397 position:13% line:83% align:start
I just sensed an evil aura
nearby...

00:13:27.430 --> 00:13:30.735 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:13:31.469 --> 00:13:33.337 position:30% line:89% align:start
Wait for me!

00:13:33.904 --> 00:13:37.142 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

00:13:37.409 --> 00:13:38.877 position:19% line:89% align:start
You're all heartless!

00:13:39.244 --> 00:13:42.582 position:35% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:13:51.325 --> 00:13:53.461 position:10% line:89% align:start
Whoa. What happened here?!

00:13:53.495 --> 00:13:54.962 position:21% line:89% align:start
[hesitant grunting]

00:13:54.996 --> 00:13:56.732 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:13:56.766 --> 00:13:58.701 position:16% line:83% align:start
Something's taken their
energy...

00:13:58.734 --> 00:13:59.468 position:38% line:89% align:start
What?!

00:13:59.502 --> 00:14:01.270 position:33% line:89% align:start
Energy...?

00:14:01.304 --> 00:14:03.272 position:13% line:83% align:start
All right... Everyone stay
alert!

00:14:03.306 --> 00:14:03.939 position:44% line:89% align:start
Mm!

00:14:04.907 --> 00:14:08.245 position:5% line:83% align:start
But what caused this? Why is
it happening...?

00:14:14.519 --> 00:14:17.656 position:33% line:89% align:start
[screaming]

00:14:17.690 --> 00:14:18.457 position:38% line:89% align:start
Minako!

00:14:18.490 --> 00:14:21.493 position:30% line:89% align:start
You pervert!

00:14:23.630 --> 00:14:24.698 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:14:30.438 --> 00:14:32.907 position:10% line:89% align:start
Those plants! What are they?

00:14:33.341 --> 00:14:34.208 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:14:44.587 --> 00:14:47.223 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's the plants! They're
controlling these people!

